HEADWORD: Monody
<hw>Mon"o*dy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Monodies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>monodia</ets>, Gr.
<?/, fr. <?/ singing alone; <grk>mo`nos</grk> single + <?/ song: cf. F.
<ets>monodie</ets>. See <er>Ode</er>.]</ety> <def>A species of poem of a
mournful character, in which a single mourner expresses lamentation; a
song for one voice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

